    </div>
    <p style="max-width: 760px; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-muted);">
      <em>Note: OAI count of 9 is identical in FY2022 and FY2023 — this is the number reported in both official BIMO metrics publications. FY2024 count of 12 warning letters is from FDLI's February 2025 analysis.</em>
    </p>

    <h3 style="font-size: 1.05rem; margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);">Most-Cited 21 CFR Sections — Warning Letters FY2019–FY2024</h3>
    <div class="compare-table-wrap">
      <table class="compare-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Rank</th>
            <th scope="col">Section</th>
            <th scope="col">Subject</th>
            <th scope="col">Warning Letters (of 42)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>1</td><td>21 CFR 312.60</td><td>Protocol compliance</td><td>25 (60%)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>2</td><td>21 CFR 312.20</td><td>Failure to submit IND</td><td>13 (31%)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>3</td><td>21 CFR 50.20</td><td>Informed consent</td><td>Frequent; co-cited with 312.60</td></tr>
          <tr><td>4</td><td>21 CFR 312.66</td><td>IRB review assurance</td><td>Increasing; 4 of 7 in early FY2024</td></tr>
          <tr><td>5</td><td>21 CFR 312.62</td><td>Investigator recordkeeping</td><td>High 483 frequency; less common as WL</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h3 style="font-size: 1.05rem; margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);">Trend Notes Across FY2022–FY2024</h3>
    <ol style="max-width: 760px; line-height: 1.7;">
      <li><strong>Inspection volume increased sharply from FY2022 to FY2023.</strong> Total BIMO inspections rose from 766 to 1,073 (+40%); CI inspections rose from 504 to 681 (+35%). Reflects post-pandemic recovery of the inspection program. OAI rates remained low (9 per year both years) — most findings are VAI-level.</li>
      <li><strong>Warning letter volume is increasing.</strong> ~6 in FY2022, ~11 in FY2023, ~12 in FY2024. Tracks with increased inspection activity.</li>
      <li><strong>IRB-related violations are a growing enforcement focus.</strong> 4 of 7 BIMO warning letters in early FY2024 involved IRB activities.</li>
      <li><strong>IND submission failures are the second most common warning letter basis</strong> and disproportionately affect sponsor-investigators (physician-initiated research).</li>
      <li><strong>Data integrity findings are escalating in severity.</strong> The Applied Therapeutics case (2024 WL) resulted in a concurrent Complete Response Letter to the drug application plus a shareholder lawsuit — illustrating FDA's willingness to use BIMO findings to invalidate NDA/BLA submissions.</li>
      <li><strong>FY2024 full metrics are not yet public.</strong> Treat FY2024 as directional data only.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

